Core interfaces and classes that define the IDDM SDK framework.

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AuthenticationOperations<IN extends AuthenticationRequest,OUT extends AuthenticationResponse>
    Defines methods for connectors that can perform authentication operations against the backend data source.
    AuthenticationRequest
    Represents a request for authentication.
    AuthenticationResponse
    Marker interface for AuthenticationOperations responses that potentially can be returned to IDDM for processing.
    ConnectionRequest
    Represents a request to connect to a URI-identified resource.
    ConnectionResponse

    Connector

    Marker interface for Request implementations intended to be used with CreateOperations implementations.

    Marker interface for CreateOperations responses that potentially can be returned to IDDM for processing.
    DataProvider<OUT extends SearchResponse & HasStatus>

    DeleteResponse

    ExtractSchemaOperations<IN extends ExtractSchemaRequest,OUT extends ExtractSchemaResponse>
    Defines methods for connectors that can perform automatic schema extraction operations against the backend data source.
    ExtractSchemaRequest
    Marker interface for Request implementations intended to be used with ExtractSchemaOperations implementations.
    ExtractSchemaResponse
    Marker interface for ExtractSchemaOperations responses that potentially can be returned to IDDM for processing.
    HasStatus
    An interface for objects that provide a StatusCode to represent the result of an operation, typically indicating success or failure.
    ModifyOperations<IN extends ModifyRequest,OUT extends ModifyResponse>
    Defines methods for connectors that can perform modify operations against the backend data source.
    ModifyRequest  
    ModifyResponse
    Marker interface for ModifyOperations responses that potentially can be returned to IDDM for processing.
    Request
    Marker interface for objects that can be processed by TypeConverter and Connector implementations.
    Response
    Identifies an object as a return value eligible for processing by the IDDM connector framework.
    SearchOperations<IN extends SearchRequest,OUT extends SearchResponse>
    Defines methods for connectors that can perform search operations against the backend data source.
    SearchRequest
    Marker interface for Request implementations intended to be used with SearchOperations implementations.
    SearchResponse
    Marker interface for SearchOperations responses that potentially can be returned to IDDM for processing.
    SequentialDataProvider<OUT extends SearchResponse & HasStatus>
    This interface defines methods for providing responses with partial data, where the data can be accessed in only sequential order, similar to a singly linked list.
    StatusCode
    Represents an implementation-specific status code from a backend operation.

    Defines methods for connectors that can test connections to external data sources, such as a REST API endpoint or file.

Package com.radiantlogic.iddm.base Description

Core interfaces and classes that define the IDDM SDK framework.

This package contains the fundamental building blocks for creating custom connectors, including request/response interfaces, operation type definitions, logging facilities, schema management, and data type handling for the IDDM SDK.
